This paper is primarily focused on robotics and grasping, which suggests that it belongs to the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. The use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for visual processing and feature extraction also suggests that it could belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision) sub-category. Additionally, the use of targeted backpropagation to identify important structures in the environment suggests that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of CNNs for generalization and the comparison with other approaches suggests that it could also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the use of a hierarchical controller for finger and palm control suggests that it could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category.
